\sum_{k\ge 0} (-1)^k q^{-2k}  \sum_{n\ge 0} {n+k\choose k} z^{n+2k} q^{n+2k} = \sum_{k\ge 0} (-1)^k z^{2k}  \sum_{n\ge 0} {n+k\choose k} z^n q^n \\ = \sum_{k\ge 0} (-1)^k z^{2k}  \left(\frac{1}{1-qz}\right)^{k+1} = \left(\frac{1}{1-qz}\right) \frac{1}{1+z^2/(1-qz)} = \frac{1}{1-qz+z^2}.
